headline: 3 Services Stocks Walking a Fine Line
summary: Business services providers play a critical role for enterprises, assisting them with everything from new hardware integrations to consulting and marketing. Still, investors are uneasy as firms face challenges from AI-driven disruptors and tightening corporate budgets. These doubts have caused the industry to lag recently as services stocks have collectively shed 5.7% over the past six months. This drawdown was disappointing since the S&P 500 held its ground.
